,Recommended,322930,12823375,"Posted: 6 November, 2014",all,jordanduc,"Nice little gem here, definitely pick it up if you're into this kind of thing. Aerofly RC7 is a flight simulator of RC aircraft and can also be used as a training tool for those interested in the real hobby. Aircraft range from miniature indoor helicopters to full scale, fuel-guzzling beasts, every one is easy to fly yet tough to master! The sim includes beautiful photo-realistic scenery from real locations all over the world with many different airparks to fly from, which all have their differences, my favourite being the variation in runways (gradient, length, width etc). Every one makes for a challenging flight without even considering the wind yet!The hud is great and easy to interpret, it includes vital instruments in a simple easy to read format which can all be adjusted to your liking from the dropdown menus, everything works very smoothly and everything feels like how it should feel. From the menus you can also customize each aircraft to your liking e.g. throws and whatnot. I've found nothing annoying about this sim yet but If I do I'll be sure to come back and update this review.To sum it up;Pros:Great physicsAwesome interfaceStunning photorealistic scenerySmooth running, high fps on ultra settingsEasy super simple control setup(Regular Joystick, Keyboard or RC transmitter of the simulator type)Plenty of great aircraftTrackIR compatibleVery customizable (Aircraft flight surfaces, throws etc..)Cons:None other than the cost aspect, I got the regular edition yet moved to ultimate as I noticed a few of my favourite birds were in it. Ended up costing me well over $100 all up.I guess in the end if you really are into flight in general, flight simming or RC aircraft the enjoyment had is definitely worth it. Like all flight sims especially those with payware they are not cheap, I'd honestly say this one is worth every penny, and I personally love it!A must have for any AVGeek!"
76561198011798933,Recommended,322930,12850953,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,Phil Ciborowski,"I am a beginner to the world of RC airplanes. I had one a few years back but things didnt go so great and became discouraged with the hobby until i saw this. I bought the standard version  (all a beginner really needs) and thought i would need hours and hours of practicing before I got good at it.. nope! I just needed an hour to learn how to not overfly my airplane, and smoothly control things to keep from crashing. Felt confident enough to go out with my new airplane today, and was more than happy to see that what i learned with this, helped in the real world...Highly reccomend to anyone looking to get into RC flying. I use a Logitech game pad (similar to PS2) and have a DX5e Radio that i am now waiting to get the hook up for so i can use it with this program.Graphics are excellent, models behave like they will IRL.  Overall a fantastic tool!11/12 UpdateJust an update - I was out flying over the weekend, and again yesterday. I have to admit that this as a TOOL (not game) is extremely useful and helpful to those getting into the hobby.  If you are thinking of getting into the world of RC flying, try this first - its a lot easier to spend 30 bucks on a piece of training software (a real steal if you think about it) instead of the hundreds of dollars on airplanes, radios and parts that you will need if you go out with out any practice or experience.I am not sure why there are people out there griping over the views  or cost.  The view is the only one you have (unless using FPV) when you are out at the field.. this isnt a shoorter, or flying game. This is a TRAINING TOOL!As with anything, start small- build from there. As a beginner you dont need the most expensive version. Learn to fly first, learn to transfer those skills to real world and then move up.If you go into this thinking you are getting a game, or that this is like FSX or anything, you will be mistaken."
76561197979058715,Not Recommended,322930,12942947,"Posted: 14 November, 2014",all,aerospin_ed-*****,"Wish I could get a refund. I mistakenly assumed they would have improved their flight model from Pro, but all they did was add aircraft and sceneries. I cannot detect any improvement in stall/snap/spin realism at all. Pretty good for basic stuff, and hovering/torque rolls, but stall/snap performance is MUCH too forgiving, and not at all representative of any but the most forgiving models. Realflight is MUCH MUCH better.  I have been flying RC since 1978 and I'm an 8,000 hour professional pilot (full-scale) with competition acro experience (full-scale)."
76561197969893764,Recommended,322930,12852445,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,Gomoto,"This is a simulator for radio controlled airplanes, but I like to fly this sim just for fun. There is quite a steep learning curve to fly a RC plane while you are standing still on the ground, and this is simulated very well by aerofly. I like to try out the many different RC planes and helis. I even manage to land two or three of the planes :-)After playing around with the standard version I upgraded to the ultimate edition. Not only the learning curve is steep, but also the price."
,Recommended,322930,12911151,"Posted: 12 November, 2014",all,Balamir,"Well as you know there are 3 top RC simulators (RealFlight, Phoenix and Aerofly RC) in the market and this simulator is one of them. I have both RealFlight and Phoenix RC simulators and I just bought ultimate edition of Aerofly RC to compare with them.To be honest, It is very hard to compare all those 3 top rc simulators with each other, they are all good and they have all pros and cons. However,instead of comparing all those 3 games, I will try to explain my opinion about Aerofly RC.The Graphics are really good and it will probably satisfy rc sim fans.The Gameplay mechanics are really good and this simulator will really help you in real life if you are beginner. Especially, I have some of the in-game plane models in real life and game really gave me feeling that I am flying in real life. By the way, I am using Art-tech 6ch simulator transmitter which is cheap and easy to use on your computer.Sounds are good enough for you to feel realism and sucks you in the game.The aircraft details are fine and realisticThe weather is good. Especially if you fly your rc models at noon you can set up the time of the day and practice not to fly in to the sun.The wind is effective and normally in my city its rare to see weather without wind, so in the game I am using wind settings to be better rc pilot in real life.Summary:Best part; In my opinion, the hardest part of the rc plane is landing and this game will really help me to increase my skill about landingsI wish; there are some kind of missions which can add more playable options with friends, the game is a bit expansive and you really need to buy ultimate edition if you want more and you will want more... In some sceneries you can not change the views. There can be more planes, especially some electric motored planes are not enough for me because in real life I am just flying with electric motored rc planes.In conclusion: this simulator is really great and it will give you both pleasure and training for RC models. I insist that you should use simulator controller (with cable if you can) instead of xbox or other type of controller. The other simulators are also great. However, this one is enough for you if you are searching for a really good simulator which will train you for real life or just enjoy multiplayer with friends."
