76561198043261815,Recommended,322930,14665665,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,valenti_scott,"Not bad for the price.  All in all, I recommend it.  I've had a lot of fun with it, and I've spent many hours of addictive play.Later on, you may want to move up to a more realistic simulator, though.  I say buy the basic version and a decent RC simulator controller like the Volantex.  If you really like playing with an RC simulator, you can later spend more money on a more realistic one like AccuRC, Phoenix or RealFlight.Heck, AccuRC even connects directly to Spektrum RC controllers at no extra cost.  If you already have a Spektrun RC controller, you might want to skip Aerofly and go directly to something like AccuRC.  Aerofly won't connect to your Spektrum RC controller unless you buy additional hardware interfaces."
